  <h2 id="overview" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400 vf-u-padding__bottom--600 vf-search-client-side--no-index">Overview</h2>

  <p>Embedding LRO in development means making performance, resilience, and efficiency part of everyday delivery from design to deployment, rather than treating them as post-release fixes.</p>

  <p><strong>Key idea:</strong> shift left for performance and resilience. Validate early during design and coding, and continuously through CI/CD and monitoring.</p>

  <h2 id="why-lro" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Why this matters for LRO</h2>

  <h3>User impact</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Slow networks expose inefficiencies introduced during development</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Low-end devices struggle with unoptimised code and assets</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Expensive data plans amplify poor implementation choices</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Missing monitoring allows regressions to go unnoticed</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Risks if ignored</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Performance issues discovered too late</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Frequent regressions after release</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Inconsistent experience across environments</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Higher cost of post-deployment remediation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="common-problems" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Common problems</h2>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Performance checks only happen near release</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">No performance budgets in CI/CD</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Code review focuses on functionality but not efficiency</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Little testing on low-end devices and slow networks</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">No real-user performance monitoring</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Over-reliance on manual checks</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="design-principles" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Design principles involved</h2>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Shift-left testing and validation</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Continuous performance enforcement</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Automation over manual checks</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Performance as a feature, not an afterthought</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Guardrails over advisory guidelines</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Feedback-driven development</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Progressive enhancement</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="strategy-options" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Strategy options</h2>

  <h3>Design reviews</h3>
  <p>Ensure LRO principles are built into designs before implementation starts.</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Prioritise content-first layouts</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Define degraded and offline states</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Limit above-the-fold heavy assets</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Avoid design assumptions about high bandwidth</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Pull request checks</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Enforce bundle size limits</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Block large unoptimised assets</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Encourage lazy loading and code splitting</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Include performance impact in PR descriptions</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>CI/CD integration</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Treat budget breaches as build failures</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Run Lighthouse audits with throttling</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Run accessibility and bundle checks on every build</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Use regression detection and release gates</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Observability and monitoring</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Prioritise real-user monitoring (RUM)</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Segment by region, device, and network conditions</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Set alerts for performance regressions</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Track retries, errors, cache hit ratios, and Core Web Vitals</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="implementation" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Implementation guidance</h2>
  <ol class="vf-list vf-list--ordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Define measurable LRO goals and budgets</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Integrate checks into design reviews and PR workflows</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Add CI/CD performance gates and automated audits</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Implement real-user monitoring and dashboarding</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Review data regularly and iterate continuously</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="code-examples" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Code examples</h2>

  <h3>Bundle size checks in CI</h3>
  <pre class="vf-code-example__pre"><code>{
  "scripts": {
    "analyze": "webpack-bundle-analyzer build/stats.json",
    "budget": "size-limit"
  }
}</code></pre>

  <h3>Lighthouse CI assertions</h3>
  <pre class="vf-code-example__pre"><code>{
  "ci": {
    "assert": {
      "assertions": {
        "largest-contentful-paint": ["error", { "maxNumericValue": 2500 }],
        "total-byte-weight": ["error", { "maxNumericValue": 500000 }]
      }
    }
  }
}</code></pre>

  <h2 id="dos-dont" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400 vf-search-client-side--no-index">Do / Don't</h2>
  <h3>Do</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Integrate performance checks early</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Automate testing and validation</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Monitor real-user performance continuously</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Enforce performance budgets</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Test under realistic constrained conditions</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Don't</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Treat performance as post-release work</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Rely only on manual checks</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Ignore low-end device behaviour</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Allow regressions into production</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Optimise only for ideal environments</li>
  </ul>

